==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from [[blog]] or web log, an online journal generally updated very often.

===Noun===
# a [[contributor]] to a [[blog]] or [[online]] [[journal]]. A blogger can write about any [[topic]]. Though often in the press bloggers are meant to refer to journalists amateur or professional who run a blog.
# a website, [http://www.blogger.com http://www.blogger.com], offering free hosting and tools to create a [[blog]]. See [[wikipedia:Blogger.com|Wikipedia's entry for 'Blogger.com']].

===Derived terms===
*[[blogette]] - female blogger

